CRIMEAN-CONGO HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - RUSSIA (06): (ASTRAKHAN, VOLGOGRAD)
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

In this update:
[1] CCHF Volgograd Oblast
[2] CCHF Astrakhan Oblast

******
[1] CCHF Volgograd Oblast
Date: Mon 16 Jun 2008
Source: Regnum News Agency (translated by correspondent VM) [edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/1015019.html>


Inhabitants of Volgograd Oblast have contracted CCHF
----------------------------------------------------
The Healthcare Committee of the Volgograd Oblast has informed the
correspondent of the Regnum News Agency that 2 cases of Crimean-
Congo hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) were registered in the region on Mon
16 Jun 2008. Both cases have been confirmed by laboratory tests.

The conditions of the 2 patients, a 38-year-old man and a 49-year-old
woman, are moderately severe without negative dynamics. At the time
of their admission the patients had already removed and disposed of
the tick vectors.

Since the beginning of spring 334 tick bites have been registered in
Volgograd Oblast.

******
[2] CCHF Astrakhan Oblast
Date: Wed 18 Jun 2008
Source: Regnum Nes Agency (translated by correspondent VM) [edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/medicine/1015438.html>


The 1st case of CCHF has been registered in the Astrakhan Oblast.
According to the regional administration of Rospotrebnadzor a
24-year-old woman from Ikryaninskaya region contracted the infection.
She has been admitted to a local hospital.

Overall 783 people have sought medical treatment because of tick
bites in this region and half of them were children. The
corresponding figure for last year [2007] was 631.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of regions reporting CCHF cases in the South Federal
Okrug is increasing. The most affected region is Rostov Oblast where
334 people have contracted CCHF. Warm weather and seasonal rains in
June are favouring the spread of the tick vectors of CCHF. - Corresp.VM]

[A map of the regions of Russia showing the Astrachan and Volgograd
Oblasts in the Southern Federal Okrug can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/russiaaddivisions.jpg>.
- Mod.CP]
